# DrBrain — Agent Entry

This is the repository entry document for coding agents. It is intentionally short:

- keep durable project facts and hard constraints here
- move multi-step procedures into skills
- move deep reference into the CLI help (`drbrain --help`)

## What DrBrain Is

DrBrain is a **symbol-driven academic knowledge graph with lightweight vector retrieval**. Ingest PDFs, extract concepts and arguments via LLM, deduplicate identities, and infer new relationships through rule-based graph closure.

The Python package is `drbrain`. All real work should happen through `drbrain` CLI commands and project skills.

## Quick Reference

- CLI: `drbrain --help`
- Skills: `skills/` — 27 skills covering the full pipeline (ingest → build → embed → closure → query → reason → analyze → cartography) plus discovery tools (fsearch, patent-search, explore, proceedings) and quality tools (enrich, metrics, document, backup, citation-styles, pipeline)
- Data: `data/spool/inbox/`, `data/papers/`, `workspace/`
- Tests: `uv run pytest -m "not integration"`
- Lint: `uv run ruff check . && uv run ruff format .`
